cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a system for multi-hop reading comprehension over multiple documents, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a novel pairwise learning-to-rank loss, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization with a multi-task learning objective, which falls under the category of deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves attention-based interaction between tasks, which falls under the category of information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a challenging dataset and achieving top competitive performance, which falls under the category of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category.
